2026-04-27 | Smallest Substring Containing ‘0’, ‘1’, and ‘2’

Question
Return length of the smallest valid substring.
	Approach
1.	Use sliding window:
		left = 0  
		expand right  
2.	Keep count of characters:
		count[0], count[1], count[2]  
3.	When all three counts ≥ 1:
		try to shrink window from left  
4.	Update minimum length  
5.	Continue until end  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int smallestSubstring(string s) {
        vector<int> count(3, 0);
        int left = 0;
        int ans = INT_MAX;
        for(int right = 0; right < s.size(); right++){
            count[s[right] - '0']++;
            while(count[0] > 0 && count[1] > 0 && count[2] > 0){
                ans = min(ans, right - left + 1);
                count[s[left] - '0']--;
                left++;
            }
        }
        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
This is a classic:
		“minimum window containing all required characters”  
Sliding window ensures:
		efficient O(n) solution instead of O(n²).
